<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06176186 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06176186 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  In the latest of a series of mounting confrontations, at least 14 French riotpolice officers were hurt by stones and firebombs in clashes with youths in alow-income housing project for Algerian immigrants, authorities said today.The youths involved in the weekend violence in Narbonne, 500 miles south ofParis, demanded better opportunities for education, jobs and housing. Likeother North African youths who have clashed with police recently in bleakurban areas, the Narbonne street fighters also complained of experiencingracism on a daily basis.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  14 FRENCH POLICE HURT IN IMMIGRANT RIOTS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Foreign news in brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  From Mercury News wire services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910624  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  92  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday June 24, 199100176186,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>